From: Julian Anastasov <ja@ssi.bg>
Subject: [PATCH] Rename IFB interface to IMQ

Rename the IFB (Intermediate Functional Block) network interface
names from ifb%d to imq%d for compatibility with IMQ-based
traffic shaping setups.

This is a port of the original 5.4 patch to kernel 6.18.33.

Signed-off-by: Ported to 6.18.33

--- a/drivers/net/ifb.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ifb.c
@@ -405,7 +405,7 @@ static int __init ifb_init_one(int index)
 	struct net_device *dev_ifb;
 	int err;
 
-	dev_ifb = alloc_netdev(sizeof(struct ifb_dev_private), "ifb%d",
+	dev_ifb = alloc_netdev(sizeof(struct ifb_dev_private), "imq%d",
 			       NET_NAME_UNKNOWN, ifb_setup);
 
 	if (!dev_ifb)
